{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I want to talk to you about something"},{"time":3103,"text":"kind of big."},{"time":6682,"text":"We'll start here."},{"time":9577,"text":"Sixty-five million years ago --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11550,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":12611,"text":"the dinosaurs had a bad day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15674,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18309,"text":"A chunk of rock six miles across,"},{"time":21608,"text":"moving something like 50 times\nthe speed of a rifle bullet,"},{"time":25373,"text":"slammed into the Earth."},{"time":27178,"text":"It released its energy all at once,"},{"time":29658,"text":"and it was an explosion\nthat was mind-numbing."},{"time":33210,"text":"If you took every\nnuclear weapon ever built"},{"time":36095,"text":"at the height of the Cold War,"},{"time":37678,"text":"lumped them together,"},{"time":39074,"text":"and blew them up at the same time,"},{"time":41600,"text":"that would be one one-millionth\nof the energy released at that moment."},{"time":46996,"text":"The dinosaurs had a really bad day."},{"time":50510,"text":"OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51699,"text":"Now, a six-mile-wide rock is very large."},{"time":54064,"text":"We all live here in Boulder."},{"time":55453,"text":"If you look out your window\nand see Longs Peak --"},{"time":57877,"text":"you're probably familiar with it --"},{"time":59616,"text":"now, scoop up Longs Peak\nand put it out in space."},{"time":62653,"text":"Take ... Meeker, Mt. Meeker."},{"time":65362,"text":"Lump that in there,\nand put that in space as well."},{"time":68123,"text":"And Mt. Everest. And K2."},{"time":71175,"text":"And the Indian peaks."},{"time":72762,"text":"Then you're starting to get an idea\nof how much rock we're talking about, OK?"},{"time":76650,"text":"We know it was that big"},{"time":77851,"text":"because of the impact it had\nand the crater it left."},{"time":80711,"text":"It hit in what we now know\nas Yucatan, the Gulf of Mexico."},{"time":84700,"text":"You can see here,\nthere's the Yucatan Peninsula,"},{"time":87334,"text":"if you recognize Cozumel\noff the east coast there."},{"time":89731,"text":"Here is how big of a crater was left."},{"time":92471,"text":"It was huge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93668,"text":"To give you a sense\nof the scale ... there you go."},{"time":96280,"text":"The scale here is 50 miles on top,\na hundred kilometers on the bottom."},{"time":100297,"text":"This thing was 300 kilometers\nacross -- 200 miles --"},{"time":103373,"text":"an enormous crater that excavated\nout vast amounts of earth"},{"time":106974,"text":"that splashed around the globe\nand set fires all over the planet,"},{"time":111569,"text":"threw up enough dust to block out the sun."},{"time":113838,"text":"It wiped out 75 percent\nof all species on Earth."},{"time":118208,"text":"Now, not all asteroids are that big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121120,"text":"Some of them are smaller."},{"time":123350,"text":"Here is one that came in"},{"time":126233,"text":"over the United States in October of 1992."},{"time":130612,"text":"It came in on a Friday night."},{"time":132372,"text":"Why is that important?"},{"time":133652,"text":"Because back then, video cameras\nwere just starting to become popular,"},{"time":137448,"text":"and parents would bring them\nto their kids' football games"},{"time":141424,"text":"to film their kids playing football."},{"time":143271,"text":"And since this came in on a Friday,"},{"time":145422,"text":"they were able to get this great footage\nof this thing breaking up"},{"time":148887,"text":"as it came in over West Virginia,\nMaryland, Pennsylvania and New Jersey"},{"time":152366,"text":"until it did that"},{"time":153700,"text":"to a car in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155154,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156754,"text":"Now, this is not a 200-mile-wide crater,"},{"time":160276,"text":"but then again, you can see the rock,\nwhich is sitting right here,"},{"time":163781,"text":"about the size of a football,"},{"time":165199,"text":"that hit that car and did that damage."},{"time":167605,"text":"Now, this thing was probably\nabout the size of a school bus"},{"time":170440,"text":"when it first came in."},{"time":171621,"text":"It broke up through atmospheric pressure,"},{"time":173622,"text":"it crumbled, and then\nthe pieces fell apart"},{"time":175745,"text":"and did some damage."},{"time":177253,"text":"Now, you wouldn't want that falling\non your foot or your head,"},{"time":181203,"text":"because it would do that to it."},{"time":182723,"text":"That would be bad."},{"time":184700,"text":"But it won't wipe out, you know,\nall life on Earth, so that's fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187988,"text":"But it turns out, you don't need\nsomething six miles across"},{"time":191700,"text":"to do a lot of damage."},{"time":192967,"text":"There is a median point\nbetween tiny rock and gigantic rock,"},{"time":196686,"text":"and in fact, if any of you\nhave ever been to near Winslow, Arizona,"},{"time":200578,"text":"there is a crater in the desert\nthere that is so iconic"},{"time":204121,"text":"that it is actually\ncalled \"Meteor Crater.\""},{"time":206705,"text":"To give you a sense of scale,\nthis is about a mile wide."},{"time":209706,"text":"If you look up at the top,\nthat's a parking lot,"},{"time":212969,"text":"and those are recreational\nvehicles right there."},{"time":215887,"text":"So it's about a mile across,\n600 feet deep."},{"time":218985,"text":"The object that formed this\nwas probably about 30 to 50 yards across,"},{"time":224434,"text":"so roughly the size\nof Macky Auditorium here."},{"time":228152,"text":"It came in at speeds that were tremendous,"},{"time":230755,"text":"slammed into the ground, blew up,"},{"time":233103,"text":"and exploded with the energy of roughly\na 20-megaton nuclear bomb --"},{"time":236920,"text":"a very hefty bomb."},{"time":238511,"text":"This was 50,000 years ago,"},{"time":240645,"text":"so it may have wiped out\na few buffalo or antelope,"},{"time":243539,"text":"or something like that out in the desert,"},{"time":246121,"text":"but it probably would not have caused\nglobal devastation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249946,"text":"It turns out that these things\ndon't have to hit the ground"},{"time":253593,"text":"to do a lot of damage."},{"time":255200,"text":"Now, in 1908, over Siberia,\nnear the Tunguska region --"},{"time":259081,"text":"for those of you who are Dan Aykroyd fans\nand saw \"Ghostbusters,\""},{"time":262286,"text":"when he talked about the greatest\ncross-dimensional rift"},{"time":264946,"text":"since the Siberia blast of 1909,"},{"time":266904,"text":"where he got the date\nwrong, but that's OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269537,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":270673,"text":"It was 1908. That's fine.\nI can live with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272964,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274821,"text":"Another rock came\ninto the Earth's atmosphere"},{"time":277920,"text":"and this one blew up above the ground,"},{"time":280136,"text":"several miles up\nabove the surface of the Earth."},{"time":282473,"text":"The heat from the explosion\nset fire to the forest below it,"},{"time":287673,"text":"and then the shock wave came down\nand knocked down trees"},{"time":290874,"text":"for hundreds of square miles."},{"time":293716,"text":"This did a huge amount of damage."},{"time":295717,"text":"And again, this was a rock\nprobably roughly the size"},{"time":298486,"text":"of this auditorium that we're sitting in."},{"time":300588,"text":"In Meteor Crater, it was made of metal,"},{"time":302589,"text":"and metal is much tougher,\nso it made it to the ground."},{"time":305257,"text":"The one over Tunguska\nwas probably made of rock,"},{"time":307588,"text":"and that's much more crumbly,\nso it blew up in the air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310406,"text":"Either way, these are tremendous\nexplosions -- 20 megatons."},{"time":315115,"text":"Now, when these things blow up,"},{"time":317188,"text":"they're not going to do\nglobal ecological damage."},{"time":320599,"text":"They're not going to do\nsomething like the dinosaur killer did."},{"time":323791,"text":"They're just not big enough."},{"time":325284,"text":"But they will do global economic damage,"},{"time":327994,"text":"because they don't have\nto hit, necessarily,"},{"time":330536,"text":"to do this kind of damage."},{"time":332069,"text":"They don't have to do global devastation."},{"time":334700,"text":"If one of these things were to hit\npretty much anywhere,"},{"time":337536,"text":"it would cause a panic."},{"time":338715,"text":"But if it came over a city,\nan important city --"},{"time":341004,"text":"not that any city\nis more important than others,"},{"time":343292,"text":"but some of them we depend on more\non the global economic basis --"},{"time":346655,"text":"that could do a huge amount of damage\nto us as a civilization."},{"time":351885,"text":"So, now that I've scared\nthe crap out of you --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355431,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356560,"text":"what can we do about this?"},{"time":358561,"text":"This is a potential threat."},{"time":360672,"text":"Let me note that we have not had\na giant impact like the dinosaur killer"},{"time":365082,"text":"for 65 million years."},{"time":366393,"text":"They're very rare."},{"time":367754,"text":"The smaller ones happen more often,"},{"time":369897,"text":"but probably on the order of a millennium,"},{"time":372448,"text":"every few centuries\nor every few thousand years."},{"time":375848,"text":"But it's still something to be aware of."},{"time":377924,"text":"Well, what do we do about them?"},{"time":379488,"text":"The first thing\nwe have to do is find them."},{"time":381619,"text":"This is an image of an asteroid\nthat passed us in 2009."},{"time":385885,"text":"It's right here."},{"time":387706,"text":"But you can see that it's extremely faint."},{"time":390201,"text":"I don't know if you can see that\nin the back row."},{"time":392558,"text":"These are just stars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393997,"text":"This is a rock\nthat was about 30 yards across,"},{"time":396254,"text":"so roughly the size of the ones\nthat blew up over Tunguska"},{"time":399157,"text":"and hit Arizona 50,000 years ago."},{"time":401407,"text":"These things are faint."},{"time":402593,"text":"They're hard to see,\nand the sky is really big."},{"time":405043,"text":"We have to find these things first."},{"time":406987,"text":"Well, the good news is,\nwe're looking for them."},{"time":409290,"text":"NASA has devoted money to this;"},{"time":411607,"text":"the National Science Foundation\nand other countries"},{"time":414032,"text":"are interested in doing this."},{"time":415471,"text":"We're building telescopes\nthat are looking for the threat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418248,"text":"That's a great first step.\nBut what's the second step?"},{"time":420838,"text":"The second step is if we see one heading\ntoward us, we have to stop it."},{"time":424310,"text":"What do we do?"},{"time":425485,"text":"You've probably heard\nabout the asteroid Apophis."},{"time":427861,"text":"If you haven't yet, you will."},{"time":430025,"text":"If you've heard about the Mayan\n2012 apocalypse,"},{"time":432714,"text":"you're going to hear about Apophis,"},{"time":434430,"text":"because you're keyed in\nto all the doomsday networks, anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437747,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":439479,"text":"Apophis is an asteroid\nthat was discovered in 2004."},{"time":442525,"text":"It's roughly 250 [meters] across,\nso it's pretty big --"},{"time":446281,"text":"bigger than a football stadium."},{"time":448614,"text":"And it's going to pass\nby the Earth in April of 2029."},{"time":452134,"text":"And it's going to pass us so close"},{"time":453879,"text":"that it's actually going to come\nunderneath our weather satellites."},{"time":457618,"text":"The Earth's gravity is going to bend\nthe orbit of this thing so much"},{"time":461341,"text":"that if it's just right,"},{"time":462767,"text":"if it passes through this region of space,"},{"time":465252,"text":"this kidney-bean-shaped region\ncalled the keyhole,"},{"time":468733,"text":"the Earth's gravity will bend it\njust enough that seven years later,"},{"time":472257,"text":"on April 13 -- which is a Friday,\nI'll note -- in the year 2036 --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476278,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":477325,"text":"you can't plan that kind of stuff --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479089,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":480175,"text":"Apophis is going to hit us."},{"time":481677,"text":"And it's 250 meters across,\nso it would do unbelievable damage."},{"time":486060,"text":"The good news is that the odds of it\nactually passing through this keyhole"},{"time":489681,"text":"and hitting us next go-around\nare one in a million, roughly --"},{"time":492676,"text":"very, very low odds."},{"time":493851,"text":"So I personally am not lying awake\nat night worrying about this at all."},{"time":497281,"text":"I don't think Apophis is a problem."},{"time":498999,"text":"In fact, Apophis\nis a blessing in disguise,"},{"time":501291,"text":"because it woke us up\nto the dangers of these things."},{"time":503900,"text":"This thing was discovered\njust a few years ago"},{"time":506101,"text":"and could hit us a few years from now."},{"time":507968,"text":"It won't, but it gives us a chance\nto study these kinds of asteroids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511606,"text":"We didn't really necessarily understand\nthese keyholes, and now we do,"},{"time":515136,"text":"and it turns out that's really important,"},{"time":517304,"text":"because how do you stop\nan asteroid like this?"},{"time":519806,"text":"Well, let me ask you:"},{"time":521352,"text":"What happens if you're standing\nin the road and a car's headed for you?"},{"time":524798,"text":"What do you do?"},{"time":525992,"text":"You do this. Right?\nMove, and the car goes past you."},{"time":528470,"text":"But we can't move the Earth,\nat least not easily,"},{"time":530814,"text":"but we can move a small asteroid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532552,"text":"And it turns out, we've even done it."},{"time":534771,"text":"In the year 2005, NASA launched\na probe called Deep Impact,"},{"time":538756,"text":"which slammed a piece of itself\ninto the nucleus of a comet."},{"time":543241,"text":"Comets are very much like asteroids."},{"time":545134,"text":"The purpose wasn't to push it\nout of the way;"},{"time":547277,"text":"the purpose was to make a crater\nto excavate the material"},{"time":550436,"text":"and see what was underneath\nthe surface of this comet,"},{"time":553015,"text":"which we learned quite a bit about."},{"time":554735,"text":"We did move the comet a little tiny bit --"},{"time":557038,"text":"not very much, but that wasn't the point."},{"time":559039,"text":"However, think about this:"},{"time":560900,"text":"This thing is orbiting the Sun\nat 10, 20 miles per second."},{"time":565276,"text":"We shot a space probe\nat it and hit it, OK?"},{"time":567999,"text":"Imagine how hard that must be,\nand we did it."},{"time":570654,"text":"That means we can do it again."},{"time":572481,"text":"If we see an asteroid that's coming\ntoward us, headed right for us,"},{"time":576644,"text":"and we have two years to go?"},{"time":578350,"text":"Boom! We hit it."},{"time":579720,"text":"You know, if you watch the movies --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":582267,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583349,"text":"you might think:"},{"time":584525,"text":"Why don't we use a nuclear weapon?"},{"time":586186,"text":"Well, you can try that,\nbut the problem is timing."},{"time":588563,"text":"Shoot a nuclear weapon at this thing,"},{"time":590377,"text":"you have to blow it up\nwithin a few milliseconds of tolerance,"},{"time":593333,"text":"or else you'll miss it."},{"time":594533,"text":"And there are a lot of other problems\nwith that; it's very hard to do."},{"time":597858,"text":"But just hitting something?\nThat's pretty easy."},{"time":600085,"text":"I think even NASA can do that,\nand proved that they can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602747,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603780,"text":"The problem is, if you hit this asteroid,\nyou've changed the orbit,"},{"time":607233,"text":"you measure the orbit,"},{"time":608409,"text":"then you find out, oh yeah,\nwe just pushed it into a keyhole,"},{"time":611360,"text":"and now it's going to hit us\nin three years."},{"time":613461,"text":"Well, my opinion is: fine!"},{"time":615613,"text":"It's not hitting us in six months --"},{"time":617506,"text":"that's good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618692,"text":"Now we have three years\nto do something else."},{"time":621484,"text":"And you can hit it again."},{"time":622876,"text":"That's kind of ham-fisted;"},{"time":624210,"text":"you might just push it\ninto a third keyhole or whatever,"},{"time":626903,"text":"so you don't do that."},{"time":628100,"text":"And this is the part --"},{"time":629766,"text":"it's the part I just love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631090,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633729,"text":"After the big macho \"Grr ... bam!\nWe're gonna hit this thing in the face,\""},{"time":638211,"text":"then we bring in the velvet gloves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641033,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642900,"text":"There's a group of scientists\nand engineers and astronauts,"},{"time":645813,"text":"and they call themselves\nThe B612 Foundation."},{"time":648270,"text":"For those of you who've read\n\"The Little Prince,\""},{"time":650640,"text":"you understand that reference, I hope --"},{"time":652632,"text":"the little prince lived\non an asteroid called B612."},{"time":655111,"text":"These are smart guys -- men and women --\nastronauts, like I said, engineers."},{"time":658847,"text":"Rusty Schweickart, who was an Apollo 9\nastronaut, is on this."},{"time":662131,"text":"Dan Durda, my friend who made this image,"},{"time":664274,"text":"works here at Southwest Research Institute\nin Boulder, on Walnut Street."},{"time":668205,"text":"He created this image for this."},{"time":669764,"text":"He's actually one of the astronomers\nwho works for them."},{"time":672442,"text":"If we see an asteroid\nthat's going to hit the Earth"},{"time":675069,"text":"and we have enough time,"},{"time":676806,"text":"we can hit it to move it\ninto a better orbit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679185,"text":"But then what we do is launch a probe\nthat has to weigh a ton or two."},{"time":684010,"text":"It doesn't have to be huge --\na couple of tons, not that big --"},{"time":687020,"text":"and you park it near the asteroid."},{"time":688757,"text":"You don't land on it, because these things\nare tumbling end over end."},{"time":692112,"text":"It's very hard to land on them."},{"time":693732,"text":"Instead you get near it."},{"time":694918,"text":"The gravity of the asteroid\npulls on the probe,"},{"time":697166,"text":"and the probe\nhas a couple of tons of mass."},{"time":699214,"text":"It has a little tiny bit of gravity,"},{"time":700971,"text":"but it's enough\nthat it can pull the asteroid,"},{"time":704224,"text":"and you have your rocket set up --"},{"time":705873,"text":"you can barely see it here,\nbut there's rocket plumes --"},{"time":708766,"text":"and these guys are connected\nby their own gravity,"},{"time":712164,"text":"and if you move the probe\nvery slowly -- very, very gently,"},{"time":715736,"text":"you can very easily finesse that rock\ninto a safe orbit."},{"time":720783,"text":"You can even put in orbit\naround the Earth where we could mine it,"},{"time":723932,"text":"although that's a whole other thing;\nI won't go into that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726750,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":727801,"text":"But we'd be rich!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":729577,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":735035,"text":"So think about this, right?"},{"time":737745,"text":"There are these giant rocks flying\nout there, and they're hitting us,"},{"time":741057,"text":"and they're doing damage to us."},{"time":742603,"text":"But we've figured out how to do this,"},{"time":744436,"text":"and all the pieces\nare in place to do this."},{"time":746677,"text":"We have astronomers\nwith telescopes, looking for them."},{"time":749902,"text":"We have very, very smart people,"},{"time":752197,"text":"who are concerned about this\nand figuring out how to fix the problem,"},{"time":755613,"text":"and we have the technology to do this."},{"time":757469,"text":"This probe actually can't use\nchemical rockets."},{"time":759695,"text":"Chemical rockets provide\ntoo much thrust, too much push."},{"time":762377,"text":"The probe would just shoot away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763963,"text":"We invented something called an ion drive,"},{"time":766038,"text":"which is a very, very,\nvery low-thrust engine."},{"time":768616,"text":"It generates the force a piece of paper\nwould have on your hand --"},{"time":771949,"text":"incredibly light, but it can run\nfor months and years,"},{"time":775937,"text":"providing that very gentle push."},{"time":778291,"text":"If anybody here is a fan\nof the original \"Star Trek,\""},{"time":780904,"text":"they ran across an alien ship\nthat had an ion drive,"},{"time":783723,"text":"and Spock said, \"They're very\ntechnically sophisticated."},{"time":786439,"text":"They're a hundred years\nahead of us with this drive.\""},{"time":788964,"text":"Yeah, we have an ion drive now."},{"time":790534,"text":"We don't have the Enterprise,\nbut we've got an ion drive now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793540,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795510,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":797650,"text":"Spock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798900,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":801056,"text":"So ..."},{"time":803788,"text":"That's the difference --"},{"time":805456,"text":"that's the difference\nbetween us and the dinosaurs."},{"time":808417,"text":"This happened to them."},{"time":810638,"text":"It doesn't have to happen to us."},{"time":812477,"text":"The difference\nbetween the dinosaurs and us"},{"time":815659,"text":"is that we have a space program"},{"time":817798,"text":"and we can vote,"},{"time":819544,"text":"and so we can change our future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821900,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":823561,"text":"We have the ability to change our future."},{"time":825677,"text":"Sixty-five million years from now,"},{"time":827678,"text":"we don't have to have our bones\ncollecting dust in a museum."},{"time":831606,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832798,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}